# üêû bug report

### Affected Package
@angular/elements


### Is this a regression?
No

### Description

Our use case is to create an angular agnostic shell that would be able to contain other web applications inside of it. I thought one possible candidate for this type of web app would be Angular Elements, since they are supposed to be agnostic and not interfere with the frameworks / scripts of other web applications.

Unfortunately, when trying to embed an angular-cli generated application within a website containing Angular Elements, we get the following error:

`Uncaught DOMException: Failed to execute 'define' on 'CustomElementRegistry': this name has already been used with this registry`

If ONE of the apps (The angular elements app or the angular-cli app) changes it's `"optimizations"` property in package.json to false, there will be no issue. Note: these optimizations are only triggered when running with the `--prod` flag when doing `ng build`

Building both in production mode with the flag set to true (The default setting) results in this error.

## üî¨ Minimal Reproduction

**Combined app index.html:**

```
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<body>
<app-custom-element></app-custom-element>
<script src="./angular8app.js"></script>
<!-- EMBEDDED APP START -->
   <app-root></app-root>
   <script type="text/javascript" src="./runtime-es5.js"></script><script type="text/javascript" 
   src="./main-es5.js"></script>
<!-- EMBEDDED APP END -->
</body>
</html>
```

**Angular Element app.module:**

```
